Calling with Conversation API

Calling with Devices API

Calling with Users API

Video

This supports the basic use case of creating a session, using `serverCall`, `reconnectCall`, and being able to answer, reject, hangup a call.

Copy

```
{
  "acl": {
    "paths": {
      "/*/sessions/**": { "methods": ["POST"] },
      "/*/conversations/*": { "methods": ["GET"] },
      "/*/conversations/*/rtc/*/answer": { "methods": ["POST"] },
      "/*/conversations/*/rtc/*/offer/*": { "methods": ["POST"]},
      "/*/conversations/*/members/*": { "methods": ["PUT", "DELETE"] },
      "/*/knocking/**": { "methods": ["POST", "DELETE"] },
      "/*/legs/**": { "methods": ["POST", "GET"] },
      "/*/v2/rtc/**": { "methods": ["POST", "GET"] }
    }
  }
}
```

In addition to the base Calling case, this will allow you to use SDK functions such as `mute`, `say`, etc. This is needed for the Chat SDK.

Copy

```
{
  "acl": {
    "paths": {
      "/*/sessions/**": { "methods": ["POST"] },
      "/*/conversations/*": { "methods": ["GET"] },
      "/*/conversations/*/events/*": { "methods": ["POST", "GET"]},
      "/*/conversations/*/rtc/*/answer": { "methods": ["POST"] },
      "/*/conversations/*/rtc/*/offer/*": { "methods": ["POST"]},
      "/*/conversations/*/members/*": { "methods": ["PUT", "DELETE"] },
      "/*/knocking/**": { "methods": ["POST", "DELETE"] },
      "/*/legs/**": { "methods": ["POST", "GET"] },
      "/*/v2/rtc/**": { "methods": ["POST", "GET"] }
    }
  }
}
```

In addition to the base Calling case, this will allow you to use SDK functions to manage push tokens. Add the device methods you want to support as needed.

Copy

```
{
  "acl": {
    "paths": {
      "/*/sessions/**": { "methods": ["POST"] },
      "/*/conversations/*": { "methods": ["GET"] },
      "/*/conversations/*/rtc/*/answer": { "methods": ["POST"] },
      "/*/conversations/*/rtc/*/offer/*": { "methods": ["POST"]},
      "/*/conversations/*/members/*": { "methods": ["PUT", "DELETE"] },
      "/*/knocking/**": { "methods": ["POST", "DELETE"] },
      "/*/legs/**": { "methods": ["POST", "GET"] },
      "/*/v2/rtc/**": { "methods": ["POST", "GET"] },
      "/*/devices/**": { "methods": [] }
    }
  }
}
```

Devices methods:

- POST - Register new user devices.
- GET - Fetch registered devices for the user.
- PUT - Update registered devices for the user.
- DELETE - Delete registered devices for the user.

In addition to the base Calling case, this will allow you to use SDK functions to get information about a specific user.

Copy

```
{
  "acl": {
    "paths": {
      "/*/sessions/**": { "methods": ["POST"] },
      "/*/conversations/*": { "methods": ["GET"] },
      "/*/conversations/*/rtc/*/answer": { "methods": ["POST"] },
      "/*/conversations/*/rtc/*/offer/*": { "methods": ["POST"]},
      "/*/conversations/*/members/*": { "methods": ["PUT", "DELETE"] },
      "/*/knocking/**": { "methods": ["POST", "DELETE"] },
      "/*/legs/**": { "methods": ["POST", "GET"] },
      "/*/v2/rtc/**": { "methods": ["POST", "GET"] },
      "/*/users/*": { "methods": ["GET"] },
    }
  }
}
```

This supports connecting to a session with the Video SDK

Copy

```
{
  "acl": {
    "paths": {
      "/*/session/**": {}
    }
  }
}
```

The [Server SDKs](https://developer.vonage.com/en/getting-started/concepts/authentication#using-the-server-sdks) contain methods for generating JWT tokens. You may however use the [Vonage CLI](https://developer.vonage.com/application/vonage-cli) to do this as well.
This is particularly helpful during testing.

Powershell (Windows)



CMD (Windows)



Bash



Copy

```

vonage jwt create `
--app-id='00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000' `
--private-key=./private.key `
--sub='Alice' `
--acl='{\"paths\":{\"\/*\/users\/**\":{},\"\/*\/conversations\/**\":{},\"\/*\/sessions\/**\":{},\"\/*\/devices\/**\":{},\"\/*\/push\/**\":{},\"\/*\/knocking\/**\":{},\"\/*\/legs\/**\":{}}}'

It is expected that the accompanying server for your Vonage application will generate JWTs for the Client SDKs. Here are some examples using the Vonage Server SDKs:

